  {
    "id": 443,
    "question": "The nth term of the sequence 3/2, 3, 7, 16, 35, 74 ..... Is",
    "option": {
      "a": "5 . 2<sup>n-2</sup> - n",
      "b": "5 . 2<sup>n-2</sup>  - (n+1) / 2",
      "c": "3 . 2<sup>n-2</sup> ",
      "d": "3/2 n",
      "e": null
    },
    "section": "",
    "image": "",
    "answer": "a",
    "solution": "3/2, 3, 7, 16, 35, 74, ....\nUsing the method of substitution\nWhen n = 1, 5 . 2<sup>n-2</sup> - 1 = 5 . 2<sup>1-2</sup> - 1\n= 5 x 2<sup>-1</sup> - 1\n= 5 x 1/2 - 1\n= 5/2 - 1 = 3/2\nWhen n = 1, 5 . 2<sup>n-2</sup> - n\n= 5 . 2<sup>2-2</sup> - 2\n= 5 x 2<sup>0</sup> - 2\n= 5 x 1 – 2 = 3\nWhen n = 3, 5 . 2<sup>n-2</sup> - n\n= 5 . 2<sup>3-2</sup> - 3\n= 5 x 21 - 3\n= 5 x 2 – 3\n= 10 -3 = 7\nWhen n = 4, 5 . 2<sup>n-2</sup> - n\n= 5 . 2<sup>4-2</sup> - 4\n= 5 x 2<sup>2</sup> - 4\n= 5 x 4 – 4\n= 20 – 4 = 16\nWhen n = 5, 5 . 2<sup>n-2</sup> - n\n= 5 . 2<sup>5-2</sup> - 5\n= 5 x 2<sup>3</sup> - 5\n= 5 x 8 – 5\n= 40 – 5\n= 35\nWhen n = 6, 5 . 2<sup>n-2</sup> - n\n= 5 . 2<sup>6-2</sup> - 6\n= 5 x 2<sup>4</sup> - 6\n= 5 x 16 – 6\n= 80 – 6 = 74\n∴ 5 . 2<sup>n-2</sup> - 1 = 3/2, 3, 7, 16, 35, 74",
    "examtype": "utme",
    "examyear": "2007"
  },
